---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="“Speeeeeak”: Musings on Language in Jewish Thought"
  description="A Jewish source sheet exploring the nature of language, naming, intention, and speech from Torah to modernity"
>
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
      <header class="mb-12 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400 mb-2">“Speeeeeak”</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Musings on Language in Jewish Thought</p>
        <p class="text-md text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-500">Matthew Miller</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Section: Divine Origins of Speech -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mb-6 border-b-2 border-cyan-500 pb-2">The Divine Origins of Speech</h2>

        <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">Genesis 2:7</h3>
          <p class="font-hebrew text-right text-xl text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">וַיִּיצֶר ה׳ א׳ אֶת-הָאָדָם, עָפָר מִן-הָאֲדָמָה, וַיִּפַּח בְּאַפָּיו, נִשְׁמַת חַיִּים; וַיְהִי הָאָדָם, לְנֶפֶשׁ חַיָּה.</p>
          <p class="font-hebrew text-right text-xl text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">וּבְרָא ה׳ א׳  יָת אָדָם, עַפְרָא מִן אַרְעָא, וּנְפַח בְּאַפּוֹהִי, נִשְׁמְתָא דְּחַיֵּי; וַהֲוָת בְּאָדָם, לְרוּחַ מְמַלְּלָא</p>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 mt-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">Genesis 2:20</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">וַיִּקְרָא הָאָדָם שֵׁמוֹת, לְכָל-הַבְּהֵמָה וּלְעוֹף הַשָּׁמַיִם, וּלְכֹל, חַיַּת הַשָּׂדֶה; וּלְאָדָם, לֹא-מָצָא עֵזֶר כְּנֶגְדּוֹ.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 mt-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">Quran 2:31</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">وَعَلَّمَ آدَمَ الْأَسْمَاءَ كُلَّهَا ثُمَّ عَرَضَهُمْ عَلَى الْمَلَائِكَةِ فَقَالَ أَنبِئُونِي بِأَسْمَاءِ هَٰؤُلَاءِ إِن كُنتُمْ صَادِقِينَ</p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 italic">And He taught Adam all the names, then showed them to the angels, saying: Inform Me of the names of these, if ye are truthful.</p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <!-- Section: Naming and Meaning -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mb-6 border-b-2 border-cyan-500 pb-2">Naming and Meaning</h2>

        <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">Ibn Ezra on Genesis 2:17</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">ודע כי אדם מלא דעת היה, כי השם לא יצוה לאשר אין לו דעת, רק דעת טוב ורע בדבר אחד לבדו, לא ידע. הלא תראה שקרא שמות לכל הבהמה והעוף כפי תולדת כל אחד ואחד, והנה חכם גדול היה. ולולי שהיה כן לא הביא השם את בריאותיו אליו לראות מה יקראם והוא יודע ממנו שהוא בער.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 mt-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">Midrash Hagadol on Genesis 2:20</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">...שקרא לכל אחד ואחד שם הראוי לו...</p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <!-- Section: Theories of Language -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mb-6 border-b-2 border-cyan-500 pb-2">Theories of Language</h2>

        <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">Origen, Contra Celsum I, 24</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">These names, accordingly, when pronounced with that attendant train of circumstances which is appropriate to their nature, are possessed of great power; and other names, again, current in the Egyptian tongue, are efficacious against certain demons who can only do certain things; and other names in the Persian language have corresponding power over other spirits...</p>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 mt-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">Aristotle, On Interpretation 2, 16a</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">The limitation ‘by convention’ was introduced because nothing is by nature a noun or name—it is only so when it becomes a symbol; inarticulate sounds, such as those which brutes produce, are significant, yet none of these constitutes a noun.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 mt-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">Maimonides, Guide 3:8</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">למדנו שהלשונות הסכמיות לא טביעות, כמו שכבר חשבו בזה</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 italic">Languages are conventional and not natural, as has sometimes been thought.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 mt-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">Saadiah Gaon</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">When we investigated the greatest principle, the assignment of the basic words for nouns, we found that the proof...is consensus...and [people] assigned a name to every existent thing, not because of anything which necessitates (giving) each thing its name...</p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <!-- Section: Intention and Speech -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mb-6 border-b-2 border-cyan-500 pb-2">Speech and Intention</h2>

        <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">Rabbenu Yonah on Rif, 6a</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">...אבל במצות שתליוה באמירה בלבד, ודאי צריכה כוונה שהאמירה היא בלב, וכשאינו מכוין באמריה ואינו עושה מעשה, נמצא כמי שלא עשה שום דבר מהמצות</p>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 mt-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">Rambam, Laws of Prayer 4:1 & 4:15</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">חמישה דברים מעכבין את התפילה, אף על פי שהגיע זמנה--... וכוונת הלב.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">...כל תפילה שאינה בכוונה, אינה תפילה; ואם התפלל בלא כוונה, חוזר ומתפלל בכוונה...</p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <!-- Section: Modern Reflections -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mb-6 border-b-2 border-cyan-500 pb-2">Modern Reflections</h2>

        <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">Soloveitchik, Emergence of Ethical Man</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Kedushah, under a halakhic aspect, is man-made; more accurately, it is a historical category... Objective kedushah smacks of fetishism.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 mt-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">Benno Jacob</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Every and any indication that the word is imbued through itself with some force, and that the prescribed formula operates with a magic effect, should be avoided at all costs.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 mt-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">Isadore Twersky</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Maimonides’ desacralization of language should be seen as an expression of his consistent opposition to hypostatized entities endowed with intrinsic sanctity.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 mt-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">George Meredith</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 italic">Speech is the small change of silence.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 shadow border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 mt-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">Abhijit Tomar</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">It sometimes happens that a word begins to mean the opposite of what it was initially defined to be... manufacture in 1618 meant to make something by hand. In 2018, it meant to make something using machinery.</p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <!-- Footer -->
      <footer class="mt-16 py-8 border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center space-x-4">
          <img src="/images/logo.png" alt="Logo" class="h-8 w-8" />
          <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">The Other Matthew Miller</span>
          <a href="/sourcesheets" class="text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-700 dark:hover:text-cyan-300 transition-colors">
            View all source sheets →
          </a>
        </div>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </main>

  <style>
    @font-face {
      font-family: 'Hebrew';
      src: local('Times New Roman'), local('Arial Hebrew'), local('Noto Sans Hebrew');
    }

    .font-hebrew {
      font-family: 'Hebrew', serif;
      line-height: 1.8;
      direction: rtl;
      unicode-bidi: bidi-override;
      text-align: right;
      display: block;
      width: 100%;
    }
    
    /* Ensure proper spacing for RTL text */
    section p.font-hebrew {
      margin-right: 0;
      padding-right: 0;
      margin-left: auto;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>